<db:section xml:id="path-prop">
<db:title>path : list&lt;point&gt;</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>list&lt;point&gt;</db:type>
<db:varname>path</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>This property defines the vertices of the polyline.</db:para>
<db:para>It can be a JS array of points constructed with Qt.point(), a <db:link xlink:href="qlist.xml">QList</db:link> or <db:link xlink:href="qvector.xml">QVector</db:link> of <db:link xlink:href="qpointf.xml">QPointF</db:link>, or <db:link xlink:href="qpolygonf.xml">QPolygonF</db:link>. If you are binding this to a custom property in some C++ object, <db:link xlink:href="qpolygonf.xml">QPolygonF</db:link> is the most appropriate type to use.</db:para>
</db:section>
